â€œJava is a high-level, object-oriented, platform-independent programming language that runs on the JVM. It uses bytecode and JIT compilation for optimized execution. It supports OOP principles like encapsulation, abstraction, inheritance, and polymorphism. Java provides automatic memory management through garbage collection and supports multithreading for high performance. Because of its security, portability, and strong ecosystem, it is widely used in enterprise and backend development.â€
